Sorted Blob Array Routines
Sorted, exclusive, self-exanding array of pointers to data blobs. The array is implemented as an array of pointers (void*) to the objects of interest and do not manage the blobs themselves. The user must also provide a function that compares blobs and returns -1 if the first blob is "less than" the 2nd, 0 if the blobs are equivalent, and 1 if the 2nd glob is greater than first blob (the same as compare functions for qsort).
